HEADWORD: Circumnutation
<hw>Cir`cum*nu*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The successive bowing or bending in different
directions of the growing tip of the stems of many plants, especially
seen in climbing plants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumpolar</ent>⟦br⟧
